":"Jonathan","meanings":["Biblical name, meaning ‘God has given’, composed of the same elements as those of   Matthew  , but in reverse order. This is the name of several characters in the Bible, most notably a son of King Saul, who was a devoted friend and supporter of the young David, even when David and Saul were themselves at loggerheads (1 Samuel 31; 2 Samuel 1:19–26). The name is often taken as symbolic of steadfast friendship and loyalty. Well-known bearers of the name include the Irish clergyman and writer  Jonathan Swift  (  1667-1745 ), British theatre director  Jonathan Miller  (  b. 1934 ), British actor  Jonathan Pryce  (  b. 1947 ), and British television presenter  Jonathan Ross  (  b. 1960 )."]},{"name":"Jonn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jon   or  <b>John</b> ."]},{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Hawise von Betuwe was born in 0889, in Hainaut, Belgium as the daughter of Ricfried Dodo von Betuwe van Betuwe and nn. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Baudry von Zulpichgau. She died in 0950, in Belgium, at the age of 61."},"et":{"0889–0950":"0889–0950","0889–0953":"0889–0953","0895–Female":"0895–Surnud","0906–0983":"0906–0983","0882–0938":"0882–0938","0908–0963":"0908–0963","0910–0963":"0910–0963","0870–0925":"0870–0925","–Female":"Surnud","908":"0908","um 0910":"umbes 0910","0908":"0908","0963":"0963","0953":"0953","0950":"0950","0983":"0983","0895":"0895","0882":"0882","0870":"0870","0938":"0938","0906":"0906","0925":"0925","925":"0925","938":"0938","0910":"0910","0889":"0889","Belgien":"Belgia","Hennegau, Belgien":"Hainaut, Belgia","Betuwe, Gelderland, Nederland":"Madalmaad","Boulogne-sur-Geese, Haute-Garonne, Frankreich":"Boulogne-sur-Geese, Haute-Garonne, Prantsusmaa","Bavaria":"Königreich Bayern"},"fi":{"0889–0950":"0889–0950","0889–0953":"0889–0953","0895–Female":"0895–Kuollut